  "prompt": "Is UT Austin a good school?",
  "response": "Yes, the University of Texas at Austin (UT Austin) is considered a prestigious institution and is highly regarded in various fields of study. It is particularly known for its strong programs in engineering, business, law, and the sciences. UT Austin is a member of the Association of American Universities (AAU) and is recognized for its research output and academic rigor.\n\nIn addition to its academic strengths, UT Austin has a vibrant campus culture, numerous student organizations, and competitive athletics. The location in Austin, a city known for its music scene, tech industry, and cultural diversity, adds to the appeal of the university.\n\nOverall, whether it is a good fit for a specific student can depend on their academic interests, career goals, and personal preferences.",
